text:
Flushing Meadows Park (Queens): the northern portion of the park, between the I. R. T. and B. M. T. "El" on Roosevelt Avenue (left) and the Long Island Railroad tracks, viewing east from 114th Street and 41st Avenue. This street later became part of the World's Fair grounds of 1939-40. Views 2 and 3 show the area under construction. In the background are I. R. T. car barns.

View 1: September 30, 1935
Views 2, 3: November 1, 1936

P. L. Sperr
